Colombia Stocks: Mineros, Tableros y Maderas de Caldas Advance

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-06-03T21:59:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-03/colombia-stocks-mineros-tableros-y-maderas-de-caldas-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 5 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index was little changed at 14,444.02, while the
Colcap Index was also little changed at 1,753.31.  Mineros SA (MINEROS)  , Colombiaâ€™s largest gold producer,
rose 2.5 percent to 6,490 pesos as gold futures rebounded on
speculation the Federal Reserve will keep interest rates low to
stimulate the  U.S. economy , boosting the appeal of the precious
metal as an alternative to the slumping dollar. Gold futures for
August delivery rose $9.70, or 0.6 percent, to settle at
$1,542.40 an once.  Tableros y Maderas de Caldas SA (TABLEMA)  , a Colombian
wood products maker, gained 3.2 percent to 12.9 pesos on twice
its average three-month daily volume. The advance pushed
Tablemac, as the Medellin-based company is known, to a new
record high.  To contact the reporter on this story:
